79
00:06:00,450 --> 00:06:01,760
Thank you, Lord Soul King.

80
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:04,210
Everyone,

81
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:07,890
do you guys have any plans?

82
00:06:08,210 --> 00:06:09,210
If not,

83
00:06:09,580 --> 00:06:10,410
why don't you guys

84
00:06:10,410 --> 00:06:12,940
try out the exciting programs
we have in Hanhai City?

85
00:06:13,620 --> 00:06:14,820
How exciting are they?

86
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:16,740
You can fish

87
00:06:17,290 --> 00:06:17,940
and surf.

88
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:19,530
I have a boat.

89
00:06:19,530 --> 00:06:20,700
You can go anywhere you like.

90
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:21,620
Surf, huh?

91
00:06:23,020 --> 00:06:24,850
Mr. Hai wants to take us to sea.

92
00:06:24,864 --> 00:06:26,290
I don't think we should let him down.

93
00:06:26,940 --> 00:06:27,620
Alright.

94
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:29,090
I'll come up with a plan now.

95
00:06:29,620 --> 00:06:30,260
Mr. Hai,

96
00:06:31,136 --> 00:06:32,700
we want to head to Haishen Island.

97
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,820
Haishen Island?

98
00:06:38,650 --> 00:06:39,290
That's right.

99
00:06:40,020 --> 00:06:41,740
That island has many

100
00:06:41,740 --> 00:06:44,210
mystical ocean soul beasts
and ocean soul masters.

101
00:06:44,624 --> 00:06:46,720
However, we shouldn't
head there casually.

102
00:06:47,580 --> 00:06:48,210
What's wrong?

103
00:06:48,256 --> 00:06:50,448
Do you not have the guts
to head to Haishen Island?

104
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:10,290
Of course I can head there.

105
00:07:10,530 --> 00:07:12,940
But it's too risky.

106
00:07:13,410 --> 00:07:16,090
If we can't avoid the ocean soul beasts,

107
00:07:16,090 --> 00:07:17,620
there's no returning.

108
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:18,380
However,

109
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:20,820
I lived on the sea since young.

110
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:22,890
There's already

111
00:07:23,290 --> 00:07:24,410
a complete map of the sea

112
00:07:24,410 --> 00:07:26,330
in my mind.

113
00:07:26,368 --> 00:07:28,928
I know all about the areas
where the ocean soul beasts thrive.

114
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:30,580
As for

115
00:07:31,530 --> 00:07:33,890
the experience required to avoid danger,

116
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:38,500
I'll have to charge you extra for that.

117
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:42,290
Rongrong,

118
00:07:42,650 --> 00:07:44,700
pay Mr. Hai the deposit for now.

119
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:55,820
I have something to say.

120
00:07:55,970 --> 00:07:58,140
All of you are unfamiliar with the sea.

121
00:07:58,180 --> 00:08:00,224
If you don't have a guide
while you're on the sea,

122
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:02,096
then you guys possibly
won't be returning.

123
00:08:03,530 --> 00:08:04,090
Alright!

124
00:08:15,090 --> 00:08:16,820
If I don't take on this trip,

125
00:08:16,848 --> 00:08:18,880
no one else will be daring enough
to take it on.

126
00:08:19,770 --> 00:08:20,970
Mr. Hai, you can set the price.

127
00:08:21,450 --> 00:08:23,060
We'll do our best to ensure your safety.

128
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:25,890
But we'll only pay you
a 10% deposit for now.

129
00:08:26,048 --> 00:08:28,688
We'll pay you the remaining sum
after we reach Haishen Island.

130
00:08:30,290 --> 00:08:31,180
Fine.

131
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:33,776
I'm doing it because
we have an affinity with each other.

132
00:08:34,860 --> 00:08:37,050
I need to head back
and get my crew members.

133
00:08:37,380 --> 00:08:40,530
All of them are experienced sailors.

134
00:08:41,570 --> 00:08:42,260
Mr. Hai,

135
00:08:42,620 --> 00:08:44,290
we have one question for you.

136
00:08:44,768 --> 00:08:46,170
Before heading to Haishen Island,

137
00:08:46,380 --> 00:08:47,620
we wish to find a soul tool

138
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:49,380
that can help us navigate the deep sea.

139
00:08:49,770 --> 00:08:50,770
You're very resourceful.

140
00:08:50,848 --> 00:08:52,992
I wonder if you've heard of
such a tool before.

141
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:56,860
I know an old sailor.

142
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:58,860
He has navigated the sea for 30 years.

143
00:08:59,530 --> 00:09:00,980
I heard that he explored

144
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:03,570
all the surrounding seas
when he was young.

145
00:09:03,890 --> 00:09:05,220
He owns an antique shop now.

146
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,460
As for the soul tool you mentioned,

147
00:09:08,460 --> 00:09:09,980
that's the treasure of his shop.

148
00:09:14,032 --> 00:09:15,290
Please recommend us to him.

149
00:09:15,740 --> 00:09:17,100
It's pointless to head there.

150
00:09:17,740 --> 00:09:20,340
Many ocean soul masters tried to
buy it from him before.

151
00:09:20,380 --> 00:09:21,770
He chased all of them away.

152
00:09:22,770 --> 00:09:23,890
I was wondering

153
00:09:24,170 --> 00:09:25,770
if the tool was broken long ago.

154
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:27,890
Maybe he was just using it as a gimmick.

155
00:09:27,980 --> 00:09:28,976
We'll only know

156
00:09:29,008 --> 00:09:30,970
whether it'll work out or not
after giving it a try.

157
00:09:30,970 --> 00:09:32,240
No matter what's the result,

158
00:09:32,256 --> 00:09:35,170
we won't pay you a single cent less
for your commission.

159
00:09:37,050 --> 00:09:37,770
Alright, then.

160
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:40,170
If it doesn't work out,
just take it as a wasted trip.

161
00:09:40,770 --> 00:09:41,840
You guys, come with me.

162
00:09:44,530 --> 00:09:45,460
Fatty,

163
00:09:45,650 --> 00:09:46,620
Ao, and Rongrong,

164
00:09:46,704 --> 00:09:47,968
we shall head there together.

165
00:09:48,144 --> 00:09:50,140
Boss Dai, you guys
should wait for us at the pier.

166
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:52,500
Take care of Wu for me.

167
00:09:53,020 --> 00:09:53,690
Rest assured.

168
00:09:53,980 --> 00:09:54,410
Let's go.

169
00:09:54,540 --> 00:09:56,660
(Antique)

170
00:09:58,770 --> 00:10:01,260
This is the shop
owned by the old navigator.

171
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:03,190
You must address him
respectfully as Elder Ocean.

172
00:10:03,190 --> 00:10:03,690
Understood?

173
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:04,650
Let's go.

174
00:10:09,152 --> 00:10:11,520
This is Elder Ocean,
the most experienced navigator

175
00:10:11,536 --> 00:10:13,930
in Hanhai City.

176
00:10:14,930 --> 00:10:15,530
Elder Ocean,

177
00:10:15,664 --> 00:10:17,050
I brought some new friends for you.

178
00:10:21,530 --> 00:10:22,290
What do you like?

179
00:10:22,410 --> 00:10:23,170
Take a look around.

180
00:10:28,570 --> 00:10:29,170
Elder Ocean,

181
00:10:29,690 --> 00:10:30,570
I'm Tang San.

182
00:10:30,890 --> 00:10:31,930
Do you have any soul tools

183
00:10:31,930 --> 00:10:33,810
that we can use underwater?

184
00:10:49,530 --> 00:10:50,530
Are you guys

185
00:10:50,688 --> 00:10:51,690
heading out to the sea?

186
00:10:51,740 --> 00:10:52,260
That's right.

187
00:10:52,740 --> 00:10:54,140
We came from the continental cities.

188
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:55,408
We're heading to Haishen Island.

189
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:57,340
We heard that you
have a useful soul tool.

190
00:10:57,340 --> 00:10:58,784
That's why we came here to visit you.

191
00:11:00,140 --> 00:11:03,530
Wait, land soul masters
are heading to Haishen Island?

192
00:11:03,984 --> 00:11:05,050
You guys are quite bold.

193
00:11:09,860 --> 00:11:10,770
Go back.

194
00:11:11,340 --> 00:11:13,220
I'm not selling it
to some brash and young

195
00:11:13,570 --> 00:11:14,380
soul masters.

196
00:11:14,690 --> 00:11:16,530
Although we're land soul masters,

197
00:11:16,530 --> 00:11:19,100
we're not inferior
to ocean soul masters.

198
00:11:30,704 --> 00:11:32,570
Why are you guys
heading to Haishen Island?

199
00:11:33,170 --> 00:11:33,980
To undergo training.

200
00:11:34,770 --> 00:11:37,100
Land soul masters, you guys
might not be able to return

201
00:11:37,136 --> 00:11:38,400
from Haishen Island, you know?

202
00:11:38,448 --> 00:11:39,570
We have no choice.

203
00:11:39,632 --> 00:11:41,648
If we don't make things difficult
for ourselves,

204
00:11:41,648 --> 00:11:43,260
Martial Soul Hall will do it for us.

205
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:45,520
So we have to boost
our strength as soon as possible.

206
00:11:45,620 --> 00:11:47,050
Form a feud with Martial Soul Hall?

207
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:48,690
You guys?

208
00:11:49,170 --> 00:11:50,380
It's more than just a feud.

209
00:11:50,570 --> 00:11:52,530
We're their sworn enemies.

210
00:11:54,050 --> 00:11:54,740
That's crazy.

211
00:11:55,260 --> 00:11:55,980
Youngsters,

212
00:11:57,290 --> 00:11:58,220
wait here.

213
00:12:15,140 --> 00:12:17,860
I'll show you guys
something amazing today.

214
00:12:18,460 --> 00:12:21,260
This can navigate on the sea

215
00:12:21,570 --> 00:12:23,290
and underwater as well.

216
00:12:23,740 --> 00:12:25,770
This is also known
as the Conqueror of the Seas.

217
00:12:26,260 --> 00:12:27,530
This is Dragon Boat.

218
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:29,140
Dragon Boat?

219
00:12:30,460 --> 00:12:32,170
So, it can dive underwater?

220
00:12:32,340 --> 00:12:32,930
Of course.

221
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:35,570
If you encounter a storm on the sea,

222
00:12:35,890 --> 00:12:37,770
it can dive into the sea immediately.

223
00:12:38,460 --> 00:12:40,220
How many people can it carry, then?

224
00:12:41,810 --> 00:12:43,170
Its length is about 12m.

225
00:12:43,530 --> 00:12:45,530
The thickest part has a diameter of 2m.

226
00:12:46,170 --> 00:12:48,290
It can carry around 15 people.

227
00:12:49,860 --> 00:12:51,460
If so, this is exactly what we need.

228
00:12:53,770 --> 00:12:54,460
Elder Ocean,

229
00:12:54,860 --> 00:12:58,170
I wonder how much you're selling it for?

230
00:12:59,050 --> 00:13:00,650
We can talk about the price later.

231
00:13:01,890 --> 00:13:03,890
You guys have
to answer my question first.

232
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:09,410
First question,
it is the cradle of life.

233
00:13:10,170 --> 00:13:12,100
However,
it can take your life at any time.

234
00:13:12,384 --> 00:13:13,740
It's generous and magnanimous,

235
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:15,500
yet it cannot tolerate being controlled.

236
00:13:16,290 --> 00:13:18,620
Sometimes, it's gentle,
and it answers your every call.

237
00:13:19,170 --> 00:13:22,140
Sometimes, it rages,
and it roars at you.

238
00:13:22,770 --> 00:13:23,570
What is it?

239
00:13:23,810 --> 00:13:25,020
It's Ms. Erlong!

240
00:13:26,740 --> 00:13:27,690
It's the sea.

241
00:13:29,260 --> 00:13:30,050
That's right.

242
00:13:30,980 --> 00:13:32,260
Since you could answer that,

243
00:13:32,570 --> 00:13:34,810
that means you understand
the nature of the sea.

244
00:13:35,260 --> 00:13:36,340
It's unpredictable.

245
00:13:36,930 --> 00:13:38,810
You guys are friends, right?

246
00:13:39,980 --> 00:13:40,650
Good.

247
00:13:41,460 --> 00:13:42,340
Here's my question.

248
00:13:43,050 --> 00:13:44,410
Navigating the sea means

249
00:13:44,592 --> 00:13:46,560
that you'll encounter
unpredictable situations.

250
00:13:46,770 --> 00:13:47,810
If, you guys are in danger,

251
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:49,410
and one of you has to be sacrificed,

252
00:13:49,570 --> 00:13:50,650
who will you guys sacrifice?

253
00:13:50,860 --> 00:13:51,620
No one.

254
00:13:52,656 --> 00:13:54,570
We have to be responsible
for ourselves first.

255
00:13:54,770 --> 00:13:57,050
We can protect other people
once we can protect ourselves.

256
00:13:57,072 --> 00:13:58,560
I know the answer to your question.

257
00:13:58,592 --> 00:13:59,980
It doesn't matter what happens.

258
00:14:00,170 --> 00:14:01,650
No matter the kind of danger we're in,

259
00:14:01,770 --> 00:14:02,890
no one should back down.

260
00:14:03,260 --> 00:14:04,050
Just charge ahead.

261
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:07,220
What a shame.

262
00:14:07,530 --> 00:14:09,500
I didn't realize that sooner in life.

263
00:14:10,144 --> 00:14:11,460
I tried to act tough in the past.

264
00:14:11,770 --> 00:14:13,500
My friends were sacrificed
because of that.

265
00:14:14,464 --> 00:14:16,384
It takes a lot of courage
to explore the sea.

266
00:14:16,860 --> 00:14:18,500
This is my last question.

267
00:14:18,752 --> 00:14:21,696
If you encounter a group of
ferocious ocean soul beasts underwater,

268
00:14:21,696 --> 00:14:23,232
and they damage the Dragon Boat,

269
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:25,930
are you guys daring enough
to fight against them?

270
00:14:25,952 --> 00:14:27,020
Have you lost your mind?

271
00:14:27,020 --> 00:14:28,170
How is that possible?

272
00:14:28,380 --> 00:14:29,220
The deal is off.

273
00:14:29,936 --> 00:14:31,456
It's not embarrassing to escape.

274
00:14:31,460 --> 00:14:32,260
Surviving

275
00:14:32,384 --> 00:14:33,690
is the only thing that matters.

276
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:34,650
Excellent.

277
00:14:34,810 --> 00:14:35,570
Excellent words.

278
00:14:36,304 --> 00:14:38,140
You're daring enough
to do what you can do

279
00:14:38,170 --> 00:14:40,100
and refuse the things you shouldn't.

280
00:14:40,570 --> 00:14:42,930
You possess wisdom and courage.

281
00:14:44,170 --> 00:14:45,020
I'll sell you guys

282
00:14:46,290 --> 00:14:47,340
my Dragon Boat.

283
00:14:47,936 --> 00:14:49,220
You're selling it to us already?

284
00:14:49,530 --> 00:14:50,810
This is not a joke, right?

285
00:14:51,740 --> 00:14:53,530
Elder Ocean truly loves the sea.

286
00:14:53,584 --> 00:14:55,290
That's why he asked us
all those questions.

287
00:14:56,690 --> 00:15:00,260
The Dragon Boat
can change its form easily

288
00:15:00,770 --> 00:15:02,020
and is portable as well.

289
00:15:03,380 --> 00:15:04,980
It can definitely help you guys out.

290
00:15:05,930 --> 00:15:07,020
You guys must keep it well.

291
00:15:08,220 --> 00:15:10,290
